name: Sandwalker's Dagger

name: Wraithcutter
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 16 or higher to create. This sword design is said to be the perfect blade for fighting ghosts and spirits.

name: Mage's Support Staff

name: The Hero's Secret
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 16 or higher to create. This subtle dagger is a great design for keeping hidden in the folds of your robes or beneath your armor.

name: Demon's Whirlwind
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 18 or higher to create. This design was originally used by the blacksmiths of a demon hunting clan.

name: Locater Cane
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 18 or higher to create. This staff is often the type used by magi searching for something that they lost.

name: The Deep Cut
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 18 or higher to create. The design of this blade is said to take it right to the heart of your enemy.

name: Defender's Blade
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 20 or higher to create. This is a very defensive blade. It could easily double as a shield or surfboard.

name: Crushing Pole
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 20 or higher to create. A very sturdy staff design for the mage who has run out of mana. In that situation, just start whacking your enemy with it.

name: Dirk of Insanity
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 20 or higher to create. The design of this dagger is so complex in nature that half the blacksmiths who attempt to create it, go mad.

name: Bright Future Blade
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 22 or higher to create. This sword design has a wish for a bright and peaceful future inscribed into the hilt.

name: Slimming Staff
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 22 or higher to create. The design of this staff is said to make the wielder appear thinner... something about vertical stripes.

name: Stiletto of World's End

name: Shouting Broadsword

name: Three Sister's Staff
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 24 or higher to create. This staff design was made to honor the three sisters of the past, present and future.

name: Researcher's Blade

name: Critical Strike

name: Scimitar of Entropy
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 26 or higher to create. This strange looking but strong sword design was made to honor the spirits of entropy and chaos.

name: The Wastelands Staff
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 26 or higher to create. "There are other worlds than these"...and this staff design was found in one of 'em.

name: Digger's Dagger
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 26 or higher to create. This dagger design was taken from a dagger found in the bottom of an ancient mine, and what's mine is yours.

name: Honor's Cutlass
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 28 or higher to create. This sword design was created by a honorable warrior who had retired.

name: Oddwind, The Trav'ler
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 28 or higher to create. This staff design was traded to Yulgar by a traveling merchant in exchange for a new belt buckle.

name: High Praise

name: Mind's Eye Rod
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 30 or higher to create. This staff design is said to focus the mind's eye and sharpen it's sight to crystal clarity.

name: Silent Alarm

name: Murdok's Hand
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 32 or higher to create. This sword design was created by the great blacksmith Murdok for his right-hand-man, who was actually a woman.

name: The Worldlever
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 32 or higher to create. "With a long enough lever, someone can move the world." This staff isn't long enough.

name: Devil's Grin Dagger
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 32 or higher to create. This weapon was designed to move so silently that the only thing that your enemy will see is your smile before they fall.

name: Take A Chance
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 34 or higher to create. This weapon design was won by Yulgar in a card game.

name: The Long Fight

name: Fortune's Heir
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 34 or higher to create. This dagger is said to bring good fortune to the entire bloodline of the one who crafts it.

name: The Hillking Blade
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 35 or higher to create. This sword's design came from a clan of dwarves who chose to live under hills instead of mountains.

name: Memory Staff

name: Death's Tune
description: This item requires a Dragon Amulet and a Blacksmithing Skill of Rank 35 or higher to create. As the story goes, this dagger design was created while Death played the designer a tune to inspire him.
